name: Super Dry test xyz
description: Each 330ml bottle of Asahi Super Dry is a delicate balance of quality yeast malt hops maize and rice. Brewed with precision the result is a rich full-bodied beer. The refreshingly dry aftertaste complements either Western or Asian cuisine. No wonder it's Australia's preferred Japanese beer. Asahi Super Dry is a full-strength, 5% ABV beer.

name: Soukai test
description: The lower carbohydrate content of Asahi Soukai (pronounced ‘souk-eye’) makes this a non-filling and easy to drink beer. Best served cold expect a refreshing crisp taste that’s unmistakably Asahi followed by a slight bitterness for balance. Soukai is a mid-strength beer that doesn’t compromise on premium taste or quality.
